  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds arguments for selecting a specific typeface variation or palette.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a lightweight `ref struct` that holds arguments for selecting a specific
variation of a typeface when calling
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. It lets you specify a font
collection index, a color palette index, per-color palette entry overrides, and a variation
design position.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap or used as a
generic type argument.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
    },
};
using var boldTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
